HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 684
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend HOPE Family Health on
the occasion of its twentieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is the privilege of this General Assembly to recognize those premier
medical facilities that have compassionately and capably served the citizens of this State for
many years; and
WHEREAS, HOPE Family Health, a nonprofit Federally Qualified Health Center, has
been steadfast in its mission since its founding in 2005 to restore dignity, faith, health, and hope
to those it serves by making them partners in the healing process and providing them with
competent, loving care; and
WHEREAS, established in a double-wide trailer on the outskirts of Westmoreland,
HOPE Family Health began with a vision to create a health center that would never turn a
patient away based on insurance status or ability to pay; and
WHEREAS, over the past two decades, HOPE Family Health has expanded its services
and reach, now operating multiple locations and offering a comprehensive range of services,
including primary medical care, behavioral health, imaging, pharmacy, dental referrals, and
enabling services to residents of Macon, Sumner, and Trousdale counties; and
WHEREAS, today, ninety employees staff HOPE's three locations to carry out the
mission that led CEO Jenny Dittes to establish HOPE; and
WHEREAS, HOPE Family Health's commitment to integrated, patient-centered care
ensures that every patient, regardless of insurance status, income level, or background,
receives exceptional care delivered with dignity and respect; and
WHEREAS, the organization's dedication has been recognized through various
designations and partnerships, including its status as a Tennessee Safety Net Provider and
