WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should recognize HOPE Family Health for its
outstanding contributions to the health and well-being of Tennesseans over the past twenty
years; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend HOPE Family Health on the occasion of its
twentieth anniversary, applaud its unwavering commitment to providing accessible, high-quality
health care, and extend our best wishes for continued success in the years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
